doc.after: Apart from traditional Protestant Christian holidays Sweden also celebrates some unique holidays some of a pre Christian tradition They include Midsummer celebrating the summer solstice Walpurgis Night Valborgsm ssoafton on 30 April lighting bonfires and Labour Day or Mayday on 1 May is dedicated to socialist demonstrations The day of giver of light Saint Lucia 13 December is widely acknowledged in elaborate celebrations which betoken its Italian origin and commence the month long Christmas season
